Oi. 23 fucking numbers you had for
bomb sight. and they're all fucking shite?

508
00:27:02.788 --> 00:27:04.749
Do you know how to delete them?

509
00:27:06.500 --> 00:27:08.437
I was telling you the truth.

510
00:27:08.461 --> 00:27:11.148
I have no idea where
bomb sight is. or how to reach him.

511
00:27:11.172 --> 00:27:12.524
So just let me go.

512
00:27:12.548 --> 00:27:15.301
Kimiko. keep an eye on her.

513
00:27:21.766 --> 00:27:23.327
Fuck do we do now?

514
00:27:23.351 --> 00:27:26.038
Fetch us some pliers
and put the screws to her.

515
00:27:26.062 --> 00:27:28.522
She knows more than she's lettin' on.

516
00:27:29.774 --> 00:27:31.335
Or she doesn't.

517
00:27:31.359 --> 00:27:34.421
I'm sorry. but she's not
that good of an actress.

518
00:27:34.445 --> 00:27:35.505
He's right.

519
00:27:35.529 --> 00:27:41.094
Ooh. I know. the villain
switching sides in the final hour?

520
00:27:41.118 --> 00:27:43.472
What a twist. a shock
that never happens.

521
00:27:43.496 --> 00:27:46.767
But unclench those assholes.
fellas. I'm here to help.

522
00:27:46.791 --> 00:27:48.643
I'm a free agent now. I came alone.

523
00:27:48.667 --> 00:27:50.979
You can shoot me in the
heart whenever you like.

524
00:27:51.003 --> 00:27:52.439
That's a good idea.

525
00:27:52.463 --> 00:27:56.401
That would go against
our mutual interest.

526
00:27:56.425 --> 00:27:57.694
Which is?

527
00:27:57.718 --> 00:28:01.680
Stopping a petulant. laser-eyed
narcissist from also becoming immortal.

528
00:28:03.307 --> 00:28:06.036
I want him dead as much as you do.

529
00:28:06.060 --> 00:28:07.954
You spent the last couple of
years building homelander up.

530
00:28:07.978 --> 00:28:09.706
And now you want to tear him down?

531
00:28:09.730 --> 00:28:11.249
Why the fuck should we trust you?

532
00:28:11.273 --> 00:28:13.710
You can't trust me.
Honestly. you shouldn't.

533
00:28:13.734 --> 00:28:15.087
But you will.

534
00:28:15.111 --> 00:28:16.588
And why would we do that?

535
00:28:16.612 --> 00:28:20.675
I know Campbell and starlight
are headed to plant your little virus.

536
00:28:20.699 --> 00:28:23.678
You can trace anyone. if
you know what to look for.

537
00:28:23.702 --> 00:28:27.099
And you baboons. you leave a trail
of banana peels wherever you go.

538
00:28:27.123 --> 00:28:31.269
I could have stopped you. I
could have killed you. but I didn't.

539
00:28:31.293 --> 00:28:36.358
That virus is gonna wipe
out the fuckin' lot of you.

540
00:28:36.382 --> 00:28:40.695
And you don't strike
me as the suicide type.

541
00:28:40.719 --> 00:28:43.657
I will be in my nice. quiet bunker.
reading wittgenstein in peace.

542
00:28:43.681 --> 00:28:48.036
That is. unless that
bleached blonde baby

543
00:28:48.060 --> 00:28:51.415
gets his hands on v1 and survives.

544
00:28:51.439 --> 00:28:54.167
You must have realized
by now granny out there

545
00:28:54.191 --> 00:28:56.336
has no clue how to contact bomb sight.

546
00:28:56.360 --> 00:28:58.320
But I do.

547
00:28:58.988 --> 00:29:00.757
And I can get him here.

548
00:29:00.781 --> 00:29:03.242
So. let me help.

549
00:29:08.247 --> 00:29:11.893
Earlier today. there was a catastrophic
failure of a vought petroleum pipeline

550
00:29:11.917 --> 00:29:15.463
resulting in a significant amount of
crude oil spilling into the Bering sea.

551
00:29:17.131 --> 00:29:19.651
Sorry. I'm just shaking off a migraine.

552
00:29:19.675 --> 00:29:21.403
But your mind is still
an open book. Chad.

553
00:29:21.427 --> 00:29:23.864
Yes. the spill was larger
than <i>deep water horizon.</i>

554
00:29:23.888 --> 00:29:25.157
Much larger.

555
00:29:25.181 --> 00:29:27.993
No. Jimmy. we don't know
when the rupture will be sealed.

556
00:29:28.017 --> 00:29:29.077
I'm hearing weeks. at least.

557
00:29:29.101 --> 00:29:31.830
And yes. this pipeline was deep's baby.

558
00:29:31.854 --> 00:29:34.499
Rest assured. he's got the
situation completely under control.

559
00:29:34.523 --> 00:29:37.276
I can't breathe! I can't breathe!

560
00:29:44.074 --> 00:29:46.303
Jeremy? No!

561
00:29:46.327 --> 00:29:49.139
No. no. no!

562
00:29:49.163 --> 00:29:51.683
No. Jeremy.

563
00:29:51.707 --> 00:29:55.002
No. no. No. no. no. no.
He's not breathing. No.

564
00:29:58.464 --> 00:29:59.924
Jeremy.

565
00:30:01.175 --> 00:30:03.361
Jeremy? Can you hear me?

566
00:30:03.385 --> 00:30:06.072
We know. Kevin.

567
00:30:06.096 --> 00:30:07.640
We know it was you.

568
00:30:26.283 --> 00:30:29.429
Why are you so certain
bomb sight will come here?

569
00:30:29.453 --> 00:30:32.057
If I sent you a picture of kimiko tied up.

570
00:30:32.081 --> 00:30:35.977
you'd hop here as fast as your
froggy little legs could take you.

571
00:30:36.001 --> 00:30:39.797
Park geisha over there.
and keep an eye on her.

572
00:31:00.442 --> 00:31:04.154
I wanted to say... I'm
very sorry about this.

573
00:31:07.408 --> 00:31:10.428
I watched every episode of
<i>undercover geisha</i> when I was a kid.

574
00:31:10.452 --> 00:31:14.790
I loved it. even the parts that
were ridiculous. racist stereotypes.

575
00:31:16.458 --> 00:31:19.753
It meant so much to see
someone who looked like me on TV.

576
00:31:23.048 --> 00:31:26.069
We watched with Japanese
subtitles. It's how I learned English.

577
00:31:26.093 --> 00:31:29.114
If you're such a big fan. let me go.

578
00:31:29.138 --> 00:31:31.616
<i>Désolé.</i> but we cannot.

579
00:31:31.640 --> 00:31:34.327
Not until we get the v1
that bomb sight possesses.

580
00:31:34.351 --> 00:31:37.122
Wait. that's what you're after?

581
00:31:41.442 --> 00:31:43.878
What-what's so funny?

582
00:31:43.902 --> 00:31:46.715
I'll tell bomb sight to just give it to you.

583
00:31:46.739 --> 00:31:48.657
I sure as hell don't want it.

584
00:31:51.785 --> 00:31:54.639
He stole the v1 for you.

585
00:31:54.663 --> 00:31:56.832
so you two could be together forever.

586
00:32:01.920 --> 00:32:03.547
But you didn't take it.

587
00:32:05.007 --> 00:32:06.216
I said no.

588
00:32:07.509 --> 00:32:08.886
Which is why he left.

589
00:32:09.970 --> 00:32:14.850
I guess. for him. watching
me get old was too painful.

590
00:32:17.227 --> 00:32:20.689
I'm sorry. I do not understand.
Why won't you take it?

591
00:32:22.149 --> 00:32:23.609
To live forever?

592
00:32:25.277 --> 00:32:26.737
It'd be torture.

593
00:32:30.240 --> 00:32:32.743
You're both so young.
You wouldn't understand.

594
00:32:33.827 --> 00:32:35.037
Maybe I would.

595
00:32:40.668 --> 00:32:43.855
Summer is only beautiful

596
00:32:43.879 --> 00:32:46.048
when you know winter is coming.

597
00:32:59.061 --> 00:33:01.105
Is this how you feel?

598
00:33:07.319 --> 00:33:09.238
Annie and I talked about it.

599
00:33:10.614 --> 00:33:12.199
We'd have to...

600
00:33:18.414 --> 00:33:25.796
We'd have to watch you
and Hughie waste away.

601
00:33:27.631 --> 00:33:31.736
Neither of us wants to die. but...

602
00:33:31.760 --> 00:33:34.012
We don't want to be vampires. either.

603
00:33:38.016 --> 00:33:43.373
I'm sorry. I hadn't... It's okay.

604
00:33:43.397 --> 00:33:45.816
We're both willing to do it anyway.

605
00:33:47.651 --> 00:33:49.570
For you.

606
00:34:06.253 --> 00:34:07.647
Jesus Christ.

607
00:34:07.671 --> 00:34:10.215
Yeah. that's pretty much
what he was going for.

608
00:34:14.011 --> 00:34:16.072
Do I even need to say be careful?

609
00:34:16.096 --> 00:34:17.282
It's okay.

610
00:34:17.306 --> 00:34:19.784
It won't go off until the timer does.

611
00:34:19.808 --> 00:34:20.976
I think.

612
00:34:40.037 --> 00:34:42.623
Starlight...

613
00:34:44.124 --> 00:34:47.020
I was wondering who
befouled the security cameras.

614
00:34:47.044 --> 00:34:48.271
Hi. Aaron.

615
00:34:48.295 --> 00:34:49.898
It's been a while.

616
00:34:49.922 --> 00:34:54.736
The lord is working in his most
mysterious ways this evening.

617
00:34:54.760 --> 00:34:57.572
I didn't think I would ever see
you in a house of worship again.

618
00:34:57.596 --> 00:35:01.201
Yeah. well. I didn't think I would ever
see you meat-riding homelander so hard.

619
00:35:01.225 --> 00:35:04.537
but... I guess we're both just
full of surprises. aren't we?

620
00:35:04.561 --> 00:35:07.874
- I take it you're not here to repent.
- No.

621
00:35:07.898 --> 00:35:10.526
I'm here to... to talk
sense into an old friend.

622
00:35:11.276 --> 00:35:12.879
You did that for me. do you remember?

623
00:35:12.903 --> 00:35:14.339
When...

624
00:35:14.363 --> 00:35:17.550
Alex and I were gonna get those matching
tattoos and you talked us out of it.

625
00:35:17.574 --> 00:35:19.844
A tramp stamp crucifix is
a bit of a mixed message.

626
00:35:19.868 --> 00:35:22.597
Especially on a shit-faced 15-year-old.

627
00:35:22.621 --> 00:35:26.726
But if memory serves. you
weren't so grateful at the time.

628
00:35:26.750 --> 00:35:29.103
Yeah. you know. it's hard to
hear that you're making a mistake

629
00:35:29.127 --> 00:35:31.505
you could regret for the rest of your life.

630
00:35:33.131 --> 00:35:37.195
But... I...

631
00:35:37.219 --> 00:35:40.740
God. I wanted your
approval so badly back then.

632
00:35:40.764 --> 00:35:44.828
You know. you were like a cool
older brother that I never had.

633
00:35:44.852 --> 00:35:48.063
And you weren't cynical. like Ezekiel.

634
00:35:49.606 --> 00:35:53.402
You... you believed.

635
00:35:55.028 --> 00:35:56.589
I still do.

636
00:35:56.613 --> 00:35:58.240
In homelander?

637
00:35:59.533 --> 00:36:00.784
Come on. Aaron.

638
00:36:01.869 --> 00:36:04.472
You know. I started preaching
when I was nine years old.

639
00:36:04.496 --> 00:36:06.915
in that moldy tent in greenwood.

640
00:36:08.292 --> 00:36:13.106
And people would come
and... Beg me to pray for them.

641
00:36:13.130 --> 00:36:17.652
heal their illness. look after their children.

642
00:36:17.676 --> 00:36:19.219
get them a job.

643
00:36:19.887 --> 00:36:23.640
And I raised my hands
in prayer for each of them.

644
00:36:24.558 --> 00:36:26.393
Those prayers went unanswered.

645
00:36:28.520 --> 00:36:30.707
Nobody was listening.

646
00:36:30.731 --> 00:36:32.667
God checked out.

647
00:36:32.691 --> 00:36:35.712
Homelander is standing in front of us.

648
00:36:35.736 --> 00:36:37.755
He's not asking for blind faith.

649
00:36:37.779 --> 00:36:40.884
And when I talk... When I talk. he listens.

650
00:36:40.908 --> 00:36:43.094
God is supposed to be selfless.

651
00:36:43.118 --> 00:36:45.305
Okay? Homelander...

652
00:36:45.329 --> 00:36:48.016
Homelander doesn't care about
anyone or anything outside of himself.

653
00:36:48.040 --> 00:36:52.228
Maybe imperfect. but he... He
brought this church up out of ruin.

654
00:36:52.252 --> 00:36:55.231
He fights back against the
secular forces corrupting this nation.

655
00:36:55.255 --> 00:36:57.483
He killed firecracker. and
you're delusional if you think

656
00:36:57.507 --> 00:36:58.902
he won't turn on you.

657
00:36:58.926 --> 00:37:02.113
Firecracker was a nonbeliever.
she brought his wrath upon herself.

658
00:37:02.137 --> 00:37:06.308
I am not afraid to stand
before homelander's judgment!

659
00:37:12.856 --> 00:37:15.692
But you didn't sneak in here
to argue about dogma. did you?

660
00:37:18.111 --> 00:37:20.238
Annie. I am sorry.

661
00:37:22.449 --> 00:37:24.076
I really did like you.

662
00:37:47.849 --> 00:37:49.351
Stop.

663
00:37:51.144 --> 00:37:53.021
You know what this is?

664
00:37:53.647 --> 00:37:56.608
I open it. you're dead in 30 seconds.

665
00:38:01.363 --> 00:38:02.674
So is Annie.

666
00:38:02.698 --> 00:38:04.658
No.

667
00:38:06.118 --> 00:38:07.911
She already took the antidote.

668
00:38:10.205 --> 00:38:12.976
You didn't go to all this
trouble just to waste that on me.

669
00:38:13.000 --> 00:38:16.586
No... But I will.

670
00:38:19.464 --> 00:38:21.133
Unless you let her go.

671
00:38:30.809 --> 00:38:32.453
Don't be a stranger. Annie.

672
00:38:32.477 --> 00:38:34.438
Room for everyone in our flock.

673
00:38:41.778 --> 00:38:44.549
<i>Authorities are calling it the
worst environmental disaster</i>

674
00:38:44.573 --> 00:38:45.967
<i>in U.S. history.</i>

675
00:38:45.991 --> 00:38:50.179
<i>An estimated 2.5 million gallons
of crude oil have already spilled...</i>

676
00:38:50.203 --> 00:38:51.788
Plenty of fish in the sea. bro.

677
00:38:54.082 --> 00:38:56.602
But most of them are fuckin' dead.

678
00:38:56.626 --> 00:38:59.355
<i>Vought petroleum promised
a thorough investigation...</i>

679
00:38:59.379 --> 00:39:01.816
You think a fish holocaust is funny. bro?

680
00:39:01.840 --> 00:39:05.111
Yeah. Payback's a bitch. bitch.

681
00:39:05.135 --> 00:39:07.655
What's that supposed to mean?

682
00:39:07.679 --> 00:39:11.325
It means I flew up to Alaska.
swam down to your dumb pipeline

683
00:39:11.349 --> 00:39:13.018
and punched a hole in it.

684
00:39:13.727 --> 00:39:15.329
It wasn't even that hard.

685
00:39:15.353 --> 00:39:17.206
That shit is really poorly built.

686
00:39:17.230 --> 00:39:20.668
What? Why?

687
00:39:20.692 --> 00:39:24.505
You killed Adam bourke. so I killed
a bunch of porpoises or whatever.

688
00:39:24.529 --> 00:39:26.531
Now we're even Steven.

689
00:39:31.203 --> 00:39:33.347
I killed one f... I killed one dude!

690
00:39:33.371 --> 00:39:35.725
You killed 1.4 billion fish. motherfucker!

691
00:39:35.749 --> 00:39:39.479
One human being who was
a national treasure. asshole.

692
00:39:39.503 --> 00:39:41.588
Not just some stupid fish.

693
00:39:44.508 --> 00:39:46.301
They were my friends.

694
00:39:48.512 --> 00:39:50.823
Sucks to suck. dipshit.

695
00:39:50.847 --> 00:39:53.558
<i>Stop. loser. bro-bro-bro!</i>

696
00:39:54.559 --> 00:39:57.104
So let's record this stupid fucking thing.

697
00:40:21.253 --> 00:40:23.755
You were never my bro. bro.

698
00:40:40.021 --> 00:40:41.523
No.

699
00:40:49.489 --> 00:40:50.991
God.

700
00:40:58.248 --> 00:40:59.541
God.

701
00:41:08.300 --> 00:41:12.029
Hey. Some kid shit on the
floor in the men's room. Again.

702
00:41:12.053 --> 00:41:14.472
Terrific.

703
00:41:26.985 --> 00:41:32.675
Bubelah. You might not remember.
but we actually met. back-back in the day.

704
00:41:32.699 --> 00:41:34.719
You must have been
yay-high. but you know what?

705
00:41:34.743 --> 00:41:37.972
I-I saw greatness in you. even then.

706
00:41:37.996 --> 00:41:39.765
I don't remember that. Chet.

707
00:41:39.789 --> 00:41:42.643
I did.

708
00:41:42.667 --> 00:41:47.231
Well. we needed to talk in private.

709
00:41:47.255 --> 00:41:48.941
Okay.

710
00:41:48.965 --> 00:41:54.113
I take it you saw the security
footage from the old folks' home.

711
00:41:54.137 --> 00:41:56.991
And you probably got the
very reasonable impression

712
00:41:57.015 --> 00:42:00.578
that I'm somehow working
with butcher and them.

713
00:42:00.602 --> 00:42:02.955
But honestly?

714
00:42:02.979 --> 00:42:04.540
Fuck those guys.

715
00:42:04.564 --> 00:42:07.501
Fuck 'em. I'm on your...
I'm on team you. big guy.

716
00:42:07.525 --> 00:42:11.529
And-and-and. I mean. I'll gladly tell
you any-anything you want to know.

717
00:42:17.035 --> 00:42:18.036
Great.

718
00:42:19.663 --> 00:42:21.081
That's great.

719
00:42:28.255 --> 00:42:30.024
Tell me somethin'.

720
00:42:30.048 --> 00:42:31.275
You got all this figured out.

721
00:42:31.299 --> 00:42:35.196
But you still end up trapped in a bunker
eating canned tuna and chef boyardee?

722
00:42:35.220 --> 00:42:36.697
Ooh. crunch wraps. please.

723
00:42:36.721 --> 00:42:42.495
And. solitude... Is all I ever wanted.

724
00:42:42.519 --> 00:42:44.789
Since way before homelander
knocked on my door.

725
00:42:44.813 --> 00:42:48.501
It's... gonna be magnificent.

726
00:42:48.525 --> 00:42:50.086
You're fuckin' crazier than I thought.

727
00:42:50.110 --> 00:42:51.462
And I thought you were fuckin' crazy.

728
00:42:51.486 --> 00:42:55.841
Sorry. are you not working day
and night to drop a genocidal virus?

729
00:42:55.865 --> 00:42:58.594
Yeah. but I ain't gotta enjoy it.

730
00:42:58.618 --> 00:43:02.014
- I just gotta do it.
- Don't pretend you're better than me.

731
00:43:02.038 --> 00:43:06.584
Enjoy it. don't enjoy
it... It's still mass murder.

732
00:43:07.877 --> 00:43:09.838
Least I'm honest about it.

733
00:43:27.605 --> 00:43:29.316
Right on cue.

734
00:43:42.495 --> 00:43:45.558
Oi. bomb sight. glad you could pop in.

735
00:43:45.582 --> 00:43:47.435
Get the fuck away from her.

736
00:43:47.459 --> 00:43:49.770
Lookin' pretty spry for
a hundred years old.

737
00:43:49.794 --> 00:43:52.106
When you blow your
load. is it just a puff of dust?

738
00:43:52.130 --> 00:43:53.441
You motherfuckers.

739
00:43:53.465 --> 00:43:55.651
I'm going to rip every
one of you to pieces.

740
00:43:55.675 --> 00:43:57.177
Try it.

741
00:43:59.054 --> 00:44:02.515
And you'll be wiping your better
half's better half off your fucking face.

742
00:44:06.019 --> 00:44:10.291
Now. how's about we just cool our jets

743
00:44:10.315 --> 00:44:15.195
and you and I have a little
chin wag like proper gentlemen.

744
00:44:22.118 --> 00:44:24.579
Okay...

745
00:44:27.165 --> 00:44:28.684
- No one here.
- I Grant you.

746
00:44:28.708 --> 00:44:30.227
it-it looks like that. yeah.

747
00:44:30.251 --> 00:44:33.898
But this-this is their hideout.
so I'm sure there's plenty of clues

748
00:44:33.922 --> 00:44:35.232
- all over here.
- Come on.

749
00:44:35.256 --> 00:44:37.401
Here you go.

750
00:44:37.425 --> 00:44:39.111
No. well. this is nothing.

751
00:44:39.135 --> 00:44:41.530
but. you know. they have to
have left something behind.

752
00:44:41.554 --> 00:44:42.555
You know?

753
00:44:49.062 --> 00:44:50.313
It's not nothing.

754
00:44:51.856 --> 00:44:53.167
